<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-09-15T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-09-15T17:00:00-05:00" n="594" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d594">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.20/489: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SLA1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-09-16T01:00:00+03:00">September
                                    16, 1939—1 a.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 1:50 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>547. Large troop movements to the Leningrad area are said to have taken
                            place during the past 2 days. For 10 hours last night tanks <pb facs="0888" n="782" xml:id="pg_782"/> and heavy artillery passing a
                            given point on the outskirts of Moscow were reported as moving northwest
                            and west.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_SLA1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>